---
import PublicLayout from '../../layouts/PublicLayout.astro';
---

<PublicLayout
  title="Connect to Claude — Mnema docs"
  description="Step-by-step setup for connecting Mnema to your Claude account."
  pathname="/docs/connect"
>
  <article class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 prose-like">
    <a
      href="/docs"
      class="text-xs transition-colors"
      style="color: var(--text-tertiary);"
      onmouseover="this.style.color='var(--text-primary)'"
      onmouseout="this.style.color='var(--text-tertiary)'"
    >
      ← All docs
    </a>
    <h1 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-medium mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">
      Connect Mnema to Claude
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm mb-10" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
      A one-time setup, takes about 30 seconds.
    </p>

    <ol class="space-y-8 list-none" style="color: var(--text-primary);">
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Open your Claude account settings</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Go to
          <a href="https://claude.ai/settings/connectors" class="underline">
            claude.ai/settings/connectors
          </a>.
          You need Claude Pro or higher to use MCP connectors.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Add a custom connector</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Click "Add custom connector" and paste your Mnema workspace URL. You can find it in
          <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">Mnema → Settings → Workspace</span>. It looks like
          <code
            class="text-xs px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
            style="background: var(--surface-overlay); color: var(--accent-400);"
          >
            https://api.mnema.app/mcp
          </code>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Authorize</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Claude will open Mnema's authorization screen. Sign in with the email tied to your workspace.
          You'll see a consent prompt listing what Claude can do — read your docs, search them, fetch sections.
          Click <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">Authorize</span>.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li class="step">
        <h2 class="text-base font-medium mb-1">Try it</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
          In a Claude chat, ask something that references your docs: "What does our architecture doc say about deployment?"
          Claude will call Mnema, find the doc, and answer from current content.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <div
      class="mt-16 p-4 rounded-md"
      style="background: var(--surface-overlay); border: 1px solid var(--border-default);"
    >
      <h3 class="text-sm font-medium mb-2" style="color: var(--text-primary);">
        What Claude can access
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--text-secondary);">
        When you authorize, you grant Claude
        <span style="color: var(--text-primary);">docs:read</span>
        permission — which lets it search and read docs in your workspace, but not edit them.
        Write access (<span style="color: var(--text-primary);">docs:write</span>) is a separate
        scope you can grant later if you want Claude to draft and update docs directly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</PublicLayout>

<style>
  .prose-like a {
    color: var(--accent-400);
  }
  .prose-like a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  ol {
    counter-reset: step;
  }
  .step {
    counter-increment: step;
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 2.5rem;
  }
  .step::before {
    content: counter(step);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0;
    width: 1.5rem;
    height: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent-400);
    color: var(--text-inverse);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
</style>
